5:
Well, what do you think? With every
stitch, I wished that you'd find luck in
both your work and love life.
8:
I can tell. It's absolutely wonderful!
Oh, thank you, Lilian.
11:
Hmmm... I had heard she was quite
the reputable tailor, but she's even
more popular than I imagined.
15:
Apparently, she does everything
from the design to the tailoring itself.
Pretty cool, right?
20:
Welcome, is this your first time here?
What sort of apparel are you—
24:
Th-those clothes! How in the world
were they made? Oh my, this fabric—
28:
Ah, m-my apologies! How could I be
so rude!
31:
I-it's fine. Um, we're here to deliver
these packages...
35:
Oh! Well, thank you. This must be my
order from the Guild.
38:
Could you please check the
contents to make sure your order's
all here?
42:
But of course! However, I must first
tend to my customers. Do you mind
waiting?
48:
...Yes, it's all here! I knew I was right
to ask the Guild for help.
52:
There you go, I've signed for the
package as well. I apologize for the
wait.
56:
Nah, don't worry about it. Looking at
all the clothes here was fun.
65:
Hehe, thank you. I'm happy to know
you enjoy them.
68:
You must be the Lilian I've heard so
much about. I know this is sudden,
but I'd like to have a dress tailored!
70:
On the night of the next full moon, I
have a party to attend. Before then,
you will make a dress befitting one
such as myself!
73:
Hmmm... Well... That may prove
difficult, ma'am. I'm not even sure
how long it will take to procure the
materials...
76:
Excuse me? But I already told
everyone I'd be wearing one of your
dresses! Surely you can do
something!
78:
How could you be so useless?! I am
the customer! DO something!
81:
Don't you think you're going a little
overboard?
84:
Are you saying I'm in the wrong
here? Who are you, little boy, and
where are your parents?
86:
...I'm sorry if I hurt your feelings, but
this isn't right. Just because you're
the customer doesn't mean—
90:
Now, now, ma'am, please calm
down. You need this dress by the
next full moon, correct?
94:
All right, I shall accept your request.
You'll soon have the perfect dress,
rest assured!
98: I'm sorry, Lilian. This is all my fault...
102:
There's no need to apologize. This is
all part of the job.
104:
Besides, you were able to say
everything that I could not.
109: ...Is there anything I can do to help?
113:
Hehe, you don't need to go that far,
but well... if you insist...
119:
Phew... I never thought you'd have us
help gather materials.
122:
You are also quite adept at combat.
It seems you're no mere seamstress.
126:
I could say the same for you all as
well, no? You're not ordinary
adventurers, are you?
129:
This is the first time I've seen
someone like Light, and those
clothes... Where did yo—
133:
Hehe, we'll have to chat after we
finish up here!
142: Hehe, I am thrilled to know you like it.
145:
A-actually... I'd like to apologize for
the other day. I made quite the
unreasonable request, didn't I?
149:
It's quite all right. Pay it no mind. I
hope you enjoy the party.
152:
I'd also like to apologize to you too... I
should not have snapped like that.
155:
I-it's fine. I should also apologize. I'm
sorry.
163:
Hehe! I'm just glad she was happy
with the final product.
166:
Another job well done, I'd say. Now
it's time for some well-deserved rest.
170:
That's true, but before that, I'd like to
continue our previous conversation...
173: Tell me, just who are you?
177:
Well, we don't mind telling you, but
it's kind of a long story.
181:
I suppose it would be faster to just
show you. Would you care to join us,
Lilian?
187:
We will welcome you in Starview
Village, Lilian.
192:
In that case, I shall prepare some
tea. I cannot wait to hear all about it.
